                            <comment id="10906" author="alef.arendsen" created="Tue, 31 Aug 2004 02:57:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve run a test and can&apos;t really confirm the issue. The test (together with the attached context) works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	public void testPropertyPlaceholderConfigurerWithInnerBeansInConstructorArgs() &lt;/p&gt;
{
		ClassPathXmlApplicationContext ctx = new ClassPathXmlApplicationContext(&quot;/org/springframework/beans/factory/config/test.xml&quot;);
		ctx.refresh();
		
		TestBean tb = (TestBean)ctx.getBean(&quot;testBean&quot;);
		ITestBean spouse = tb.getSpouse();
		
		assertEquals(98, spouse.getAge());
	}

&lt;p&gt;It uses a slightly modified version of the org.springframework.beans.TestBean class (added a constructor that takes a TestBean as argument and assigning it to the spouse proeprty). Also attached the modified TestBean.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alef&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
